dialogues.text: You approach what looks to be a train station
Welcome to the Electron Transport Station! Your job? Guide electrons through the chain, pump protons, and generate ATP—the energy currency of life! No pressure, right?
Here’s how it works: Electrons need to be assigned to the correct stations—Complex I through IV—to keep the transport moving.
Each station helps pump protons across the membrane, setting the stage for ATP production.
But be careful! If you mess up the sequence, energy production slows, and we don’t want a power outage in the cell, do we?
Keep the electrons flowing, collect enough protons, and let ATP Synthase do its magic. Let’s get this energy factory running at full speed!
